The paper deals with updating probabilities in Bayesian networks, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of coherence arguments and the theory of imprecise probabilities suggests that the paper may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the application of the new rule to expert knowledge and classification suggests that it may also belong to the social and information sciences (cs.SI) sub-category.
